es with great business characteristics which by their nature offer a margin of safety a truly fine business requires few assets to produce a consistently expanding stream of income svf also purchases shares which are temporarily outoffavor and selling below intrinsic value a common thread in svf investments is that the market price is below what a corporate or entrepreneurial buyer might be willing to pay for the entire business the auction nature and the inefficiencies of the stock market are such that svf can often buy a minority interest in a fine company at a small fraction of the price per share necessary to acquire the entire company   past performance does not guarantee future results mutual fund investing involves risk principal loss is possible the fund’s investments in small and mid capitalization companies could experience greater volatility than investments in largecapitalization companies prospective investors should read the prospectus carefully and consider the fund’s investment objectives risks charges and expenses carefully before investing the prospectus which can be obtained by calling  or online at wwwschwartzvaluefocusedfundcom contains this and other important information distributed by ultimus fund distributors llc quarterly fund fact sheet prospectus quarterly commentary account application ira application roth ira application annual report semiannual report statement of additional information xbrl account access shareholders financial professionals schwartz value focused fund facts  figures learn more  “value investing consists of nothing more than purchasing a future stream of earnings at an attractive price” — rick platte cfa finra’s brokercheck check the background of ultimus fund distributors llc on finra’s brokercheck copyright  schwartz investment counsel inc all rights reserved  west ann arbor trail • suite  • plymouth mi  •  about investing contact you are now leaving the schwartz investment counsel inc website and accessing the schw